 :tx/rationale "UNSOUNDNESS-LEDGER-9: C8 substrate independence violation in methodology.rs. The kernel module methodology.rs (1,396 LOC) contains DDIS-specific hardcoded weights: INV/ADR/NEG category detection, spec language pattern matching (contains 'INV-' or 'ADR-'), methodology scoring that assumes the DDIS ontology. The C8 constraint says: 'The braid kernel must not contain logic specific to any programming language, test framework, specification format, or project methodology — including DDIS itself.' Test: 'would this code make sense for a React project with Jest tests and Jira tickets?' Answer: no — methodology.rs looks for INV- and ADR- prefixes that don't exist in Jira. Some guidance.rs functions also have DDIS-specific scoring (lines 2706+: ISP projection weights hardcoded for Intent/Spec/Impl). The fix is: move methodology-specific scoring into policy.rs (which already exists for policy manifest weights). Non-DDIS projects would provide a different policy manifest with different ontology patterns and weights. This is not blocking Phase A but it is a genuine constraint violation that should be addressed."
